The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques for image augmentation in medical imaging classification tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel joint-training deep reinforcement learning framework, which involves optimizing policies using policy gradient methods, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep reinforcement learning also suggests that the paper may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of segmentation networks, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.DL) applications.
